Head On Collision

Aired on 11/16/2005, Narrated by Jonathan Aris. (the first of three "Crash Scene Investigation" episodes)

On 8 February 1986, a Via Rail passenger train consisting of 3 locomotives (one inoperative) and 11 cars, and, a 118 car Canadian National Railway freight train consisting of 3 locomotives and 115 cars, collide, killing 23 people.
